    "Let me analyze the reaction to identify the roles of reagents, solvent, and catalyst.\n\nThe reaction is:\nC1CCOC1.Cc1ccc(S(=O)(=O)Oc2ccc(Br)cc2Br)cc1.O.[Cl-].[Li+].[Cl-].[NH4+].[Zn] >> Cc1ccc(S(=O)(=O)Oc2ccc(Br)cc2)cc1\n\nSo the reactants are:\n1. C1CCOC1 - THF (tetrahydrofuran) - this is a solvent\n2. Cc1ccc(S(=O)(=O)Oc2ccc(Br)cc2Br)cc1 - the substrate (4-methylphenyl 3,5-dibromophenyl sulfonate) - this is the main reactant\n3. O - water - likely part of the aqueous workup or solvent system\n4. [Cl-].[Li+] - LiCl - reagent\n5. [Cl-].[NH4+] - NH4Cl - reagent\n6. [Zn] - zinc metal - reagent\n\nThe transformation: One Br on the phenyl ring is removed (replaced with H). This is a reductive dehalogenation.\n\nLooking at the mapped reaction: The Br at position c16 is removed (replaced with H), while the Br at c13 (Br:14) stays.\n\nThis is a selective reductive dehalogenation using zinc. The typical conditions for selective zinc-mediated dehalogenation use:\n- Zn as the reducing agent (reagent)\n- NH4Cl as a proton source/activator (reagent)\n- LiCl as an additive (reagent)\n- THF as solvent\n- H2O as co-solvent or part of the solvent system\n\nSo the roles are:\n- THF (C1CCOC1): solvent\n- Cc1ccc(S(=O)(=O)Oc2ccc(Br)cc2Br)cc1: substrate/reactant\n- Zn: reagent (reducing agent)\n- NH4Cl: reagent (proton source)\n- LiCl: reagent (additive)\n- H2O: co-solvent or reagent\n\nLet me format this as a condition_role_mapping."
